# Environment Configuration Template

# This is a template file showing required GitHub Secrets
# DO NOT commit actual values to the repository
# Add these as GitHub repository secrets instead
# NOTE: Remove the placeholder text and angle brackets when using actual values

# ==============================================
# SSH Connection Details
# ==============================================

SSH_PRIVATE_KEY=YOUR_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE
# Generate with: ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "github-deploy@sag4wd.com"
# Copy entire content of the private key file (including BEGIN and END lines)

SSH_HOST=YOUR_SERVER_IP_OR_HOSTNAME
# Example: 123.45.67.89 or sag4wd.com

SSH_USER=YOUR_SSH_USERNAME
# Example: sag4wd or root

SSH_PORT=22
# Default SSH port is 22, change if using custom port

# ==============================================
# Deployment Configuration
# ==============================================

DEPLOY_PATH=/home/sag4wd/public_html
# This is configured in the workflow, change if needed

# ==============================================
# How to Add These Secrets to GitHub
# ==============================================

# 1. Go to your repository on GitHub
# 2. Click Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 3. Click "New repository secret"
# 4. Add each secret:
#    - Name: SSH_PRIVATE_KEY
#    - Value: (paste your private key content)
# 5. Repeat for each secret above

# ==============================================
# Server Setup Requirements
# ==============================================

# Your Contabo server needs:
# - Apache web server installed and running
# - SSH access enabled
# - Public key authentication configured
# - Required Apache modules enabled:
#   - mod_rewrite
#   - mod_deflate
#   - mod_expires
#   - mod_headers

# Enable Apache modules:
# sudo a2enmod rewrite deflate expires headers
# sudo systemctl restart apache2

# ==============================================
# Testing SSH Connection
# ==============================================

# Test your SSH connection before deploying:
# ssh -i /path/to/your/private/key user@your-server

# If successful, you can add the credentials to GitHub secrets
